Police have recovered the missing vehicle for the woman who was allegedly killed and her body dumped near a dam in Juja. The vehicle, Mercedes Benz is being held at Ngewa police post in Kwamaiko village Githunguri sub-county. The victim Mary Kamangara left her residence at Safari Park Gardens for Kahawa Sukari where she owned hardware when she vanished. Her body was found a day later at Courtesy beach situated at Mugutha area in Juja with visible head injuries. Kamangara, 39, was found a deep wound in the head. Police said it was inflicted by a blunt object. Her hands had bruises. The mother of two, lived with her husband at their Garden Estate home in Nairobi. More to follow.... Click here for the latest political news  